<p class="content__abstract">
  Your website is looking pretty bare at the moment. You will use HTML to structure your web page. Before you start to write your code, this article introduces HTML, the language of the web. Read it to learn what HTML tags are and which ones to use, when. You won't type anything in your new web app whilst reading this article.
</p>

<h2 id="html-tags">HTML tags</h2>
<p><a href="glossary#html">HTML</a> is composed of HTML tags that go at the start and the finish of the content that you want to mark up. They come in two parts: an opening HTML tag such as <code class="highlighter-rouge">&lt;p&gt;</code>, and a closing HTML tag such as <code class="highlighter-rouge">&lt;/p&gt;</code>, (notice the <code class="highlighter-rouge">/</code> before the <code class="highlighter-rouge">p</code>).</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>It‚Äôs a bit like the old advice for giving a speech: ‚ÄúTell ‚Äôem what you‚Äôre going to tell ‚Äôem; tell ‚Äôem; tell ‚Äôem what you‚Äôve told ‚Äôem‚Äù. Or the age-old advice for good storytelling ‚Äì have a beginning, a middle, and an end:</p>

  <p><code class="highlighter-rouge">&lt;p&gt;</code> means there‚Äôs a paragraph coming up.</p>

  <p>Then there‚Äôs a paragraph.</p>

  <p>Then <code class="highlighter-rouge">&lt;/p&gt;</code> means that we just had a paragraph, and now it‚Äôs over.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Here‚Äôs a list of HTML tags. You will use them to tell the browser how it should structure your page.</p>

<p><strong>Paragraph</strong></p>

<p>Here is an example of paragraph <code class="highlighter-rouge">&lt;p&gt;</code> <code class="highlighter-rouge">&lt;/p&gt;</code> tags in action:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-html" data-lang="html"><table class="rouge-table"><tbody><tr><td class="gutter gl"><pre class="lineno">1
2
3
4
</pre></td><td class="code"><pre>  <span class="nt">&lt;p&gt;</span>
    An anthologie of fine stories
    inspir‚Äôd by the Bard of Stratford and the Lovecraftian Mythos
  <span class="nt">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
</pre></td></tr></tbody></table></code></pre></figure>

<p>Which display in a browser as:</p>

<div class="display-box">
  <p class="display">
    An anthologie of fine stories
    inspir‚Äôd by the Bard of Stratford
    and the Lovecraftian Mythos
  </p>
</div>

<p><strong>Strong</strong></p>

<p>Here is an example of strong <code class="highlighter-rouge">&lt;strong&gt;</code> <code class="highlighter-rouge">&lt;/strong&gt;</code> tags in action:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-html" data-lang="html"><table class="rouge-table"><tbody><tr><td class="gutter gl"><pre class="lineno">1
2
3
4
5
</pre></td><td class="code"><pre>  <span class="nt">&lt;p&gt;</span>
    An anthologie of fine stories
    inspir‚Äôd by the <span class="nt">&lt;strong&gt;</span>Bard of Stratford<span class="nt">&lt;/strong&gt;</span>
    and the Lovecraftian Mythos
  <span class="nt">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
</pre></td></tr></tbody></table></code></pre></figure>

<p>Which display in a browser as:</p>

<div class="display-box">
  <p class="display">
    An anthologie of fine stories
    inspir‚Äôd by the <strong>Bard of Stratford</strong>
    and the Lovecraftian Mythos
  </p>
</div>

<p><strong>Headings</strong></p>

<p>Here is an example of heading tags in action:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-html" data-lang="html"><table class="rouge-table"><tbody><tr><td class="gutter gl"><pre class="lineno">1
