<p><strong>Image</strong></p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-html" data-lang="html"><table class="rouge-table"><tbody><tr><td class="gutter gl"><pre class="lineno">1
</pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="nt">&lt;img</span> <span class="na">src=</span><span class="s">'/assets/images/cover.png'</span> <span class="na">alt=</span><span class="s">'Shakespeare vs Cthulhu cover image'</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span>
</pre></td></tr></tbody></table></code></pre></figure>

<p>Code which points to a file location of an image to display. <code class="highlighter-rouge">src</code> means source ‚Äì the file location. <code class="highlighter-rouge">alt</code> means alternative text ‚Äì vital for accessibility. The <code class="highlighter-rouge">img</code> tag is self closing ‚Äì you don‚Äôt put an <code class="highlighter-rouge">&lt;/img&gt;</code> tag at the end.</p>

<div class="display-box">
  <div class="display">
     <img src="/assets/images/cover.png" alt="Shakespeare vs Cthulhu cover image" />
  </div>
</div>

